{
  "doc_id": "26916",
  "text": "Synthesis of extracellular matrices component (i.e. collagen, elastin, and hyaluronic acid) in HFF-1 was estimated for determining the potential of the Biofield Energy Treated test formulation and DMEM to improve skin strength, elasticity and hydration level. HFF-1 cells were counted using hemocytometer and plated in 48 well plates at the density corresponding to 10 X 10 3 cells/well in DMEM supplemented with 15% FBS. The cells were incubated overnight under specified growth conditions followed by cells to serum stripping. Further, the cells were treated with different groups viz. vehicle control (DMSO-0.05%), positive control (ascorbic acid, at 10 µM concentration), and the test samples treatment at different concentrations. Further, after 72 hours of incubation with the test samples and positive control, the supernatants from all the cell plates were taken out and collected in pre-labeled centrifuge tubes for the estimation elastin and hyaluronic acid levels. However, the corresponding cell layers were processed for the estimation of collagen level using Direct Sirius red dye binding assay [CITATION_1] . Elastin and hyaluronic acid were estimated using ELISA kits from Cusabio Biotech Co. Ltd., Human Elastin ELN Elisa kit 96T and Human Hyaluronic Acid, Elisa kit 96T, respectively [CITATION_2] .",
